Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 07 of Hip MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Musculature' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'Localization' dropdown menu is enabled

And 'Proximal enthesis' radio button is enabled
And 'Prox. myotendinous junction' radio button is enabled
And 'Proximal third' radio button is enabled
And 'Middle third' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal third' radio button is enabled
And 'Dist. myotendinous junction' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal enthesis' radio button is enabled

And 'Muscle lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Haematoma' radio button is enabled
And 'Further findings' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Muscle lesion' radio button
Then 'Muscular edema' radio button is enabled
And 'Muscle fiber rupture (type IIIa)' radio button is enabled
And 'Torn muscle bundle (type IIIb)' radio button is enabled
And 'Torn muscle/tendon rupture (type IV)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Muscle fiber rupture (type IIIa)' radio button
Then 'Maximum diameter ofrupture < 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Torn muscle bundle (type IIIb)' radio button
Then 'Maximum diameter of the rupture â‰¥ 5 mm' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Torn muscle/tendon rupture (type IV)' radio button
Then 'Retraction' input field is enabled
And 'Wavy course of the fibers' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bony avulsion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intracortical edema' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Bony avulsion' checkbox
Then 'Anterior superior iliac spine' radio button is enabled
And 'Anterior inferior iliac spine' radio button is enabled
And 'Ischial tuberosity' radio button is enabled
And 'Lesser trochanter' radio button is enabled
And 'Posterior femoral diaphysis' radio button is enabled
